<p>Dan Mall is an award-winning art director and designer, based in Brooklyn. He's currently a Design Director at <a href="http://www.bigspaceship.com/">Big Spaceship</a>, former Interactive Director at <a href="http://happycog.com/">Happy Cog</a>, technical editor for <a href="http://www.alistapart.com/">A List Apart</a> and co-founder of <a href="http://typedia.com/">Typedia</a> and <a href="http://www.swfir.com/">swfIR</a>. Besides speaking at conferences like SXSW, An Event Apart, and Future of Web Design, Dan has taught advertising at the Miami Ad School, web and graphic design at the Philadelphia University of the Arts, and Flash at the NY School of Visual Arts. His clients include the likes of Google, Crayola, HP, Lucasfilm, Microsoft, GE, Wrigley, The Mozilla Foundation, Thomson Reuters, and The Sherwin-Williams Company.</p>
<p>Dan writes about design on <a href="http://danielmall.com/">his site</a>, and tweets as <a href="http://twitter.com/#!/danielmall">@danielmall</a>.</p>